					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I just trough something.
<br />You should detect blank tiles and make them point to the same actual tiles. So if your image contains enough "blanks" areas, you could get a larger surface and still deal with the 256-tile limit.
<br />The problem is that you then have to write to name table as well, as if pattern tables aren't enough.
<br />
<br />Also, in a FMV, video, chances are that  a frame will be very similar to the frame just before that. Using this cleverly would save you a lot of trouble I guess.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
